© Good On You
We are committed to safeguarding the privacy of Good On You users including users of the Good On You app, website visitors, social media and any other digital products or tools that we develop; this policy sets out how we will treat your personal information.
The personal information we collect might include your name, address, email address, IP address, and information regarding what pages are accessed and when.
Our website and app uses cookies. By using our website and agreeing to this policy, you consent to our use of cookies in accordance with the terms of this policy.
1. What information do we collect?
We may collect, store and use the following kinds of personal information:
information about your computer or mobile device and about your visits to and use of the Good On You website or app (which may include your IP address, geographical location, device and/or browser type and version, operating system, referral source, the length of visit, page views and website and app navigation);
information relating to any transactions carried out between you and us on or in relation to the Good On You app, website, browser extension or any other digital product that you agree to use, including information relating to any purchases you make from us;
information that you provide to us for the purpose of subscribing to our app, website services, email notifications, and newsletters (including your country or region and email address);
information submitted as evidence, including via any app or digital product or tool, for the purpose of Good On You assigning, reviewing or adjusting a rating; and
any information that you choose to send to us when contacting us using any contact form on our app, digital product or tool, website, any independent contact form that we establish (for example for job applications or as part of a survey or competition), via our social media channels, by email, phone, or in person.
If you are a customer of Good On You and purchase a product or service from us, your payment information is not normally held by us, it is collected by our third-party payment processors (currently Stripe), who specialise in the secure online capture and processing of credit/debit card transactions. For more information on Stripes’ privacy policy, see the official Stripe privacy page.
We do not knowingly collect or store any personal information about children under the age of 16 and we do not offer any of our products or services directly to children under the age of 13.
2. Cookies on website
What Are Cookies
The Good On You app and web site use cookies, which are tiny files that are added to improve your experience. This page describes what information they gather, how we use it and why we sometimes need to store these cookies. We will also share how you can prevent these cookies from being stored however this may downgrade or ‘break’ certain elements of the intended functionality. For more general information on cookies see the Wikipedia article on HTTP Cookies.
How We Use Cookies
We use cookies for a variety of reasons detailed below. Unfortunately, in most cases, there are no industry standard options for disabling cookies without completely disabling the functionality and features they add. It is recommended that you leave on all cookies if you are not sure whether you need them or not in case they are used to provide a service that you use.
Disabling Cookies
You can prevent the setting of cookies while browsing the web by adjusting the settings on your browser (see your browser Help for how to do this). Be aware that disabling cookies will affect the functionality of this and many other websites that you visit. Therefore it is recommended that you do not disable cookies.
The Cookies We Set
Our website offers email subscriptions and cookies may be used to remember if you are already registered and whether to show certain notifications which might only be valid to subscribed/unsubscribed users. The site has the potential to offer eCommerce services and may in the future offer eCommerce and payment facilities, and some cookies are essential to ensure that your order is remembered between pages so that we can process it properly. When you submit data to us through a form such as that found on our contact page, cookies may be set to remember your details for future correspondence. These do not apply if we do not offer eCommerce services or if you choose not to use them.
Third-Party Cookies
In some special cases, we also use cookies provided by trusted third parties. The following section details which third-party cookies you might encounter through this site.
Customization of our online services and advert targeting
We may use the information you give us about yourself and the information we collect via cookies when you use our online services to build up a picture of your interests. We may then use this information to try to make sure that when we send you marketing communications and when you visit our websites or use our app or online services or digital products or tools, you don’t miss content, updates, offers and other information that might interest you. This information may also be used by our third party advertising agencies and networks, to advertise our own or third party products and services to you when you visit third party websites and online services. Good On You is aware of its privacy and data law obligations relating to the use and disclosure of this information, and is committed to complying with all applicable regulations in the various jurisdictions in which it operates. This is called advert targeting or interest-based advertising. For more information on how to reject targeted advertising or interest-based advertising cookies please refer to balance of this privacy and cookie policy.
Affiliate marketing
Good On You digital properties contain links to third party brands and retailers with which we have an affiliate marketing relationship. Tracking links and cookies are used to identify users on Good On You properties who subsequently make purchases on partner websites, in order to charge those partners commission on sales referred from Good On You. The following data may be processed by Good On You:
Unique Transaction ID
Date / time
Purchase order ID
Purchase amount
Purchase currency
Unique click ID
IP address
The Good On You affiliate network is operated using
Tune
and
Everflow
third party affiliate tracking software. We have a data processing agreement (DPA) with both Tune and Everflow which is designed to ensure such processing is conducted in accordance with applicable laws, including EU Data Protection Legislation, and with due respect for the rights and freedoms of individuals whose Personal Data is processed.
You can opt-out of this tracking on Good On You by deleting cookies in your browser associated with the following domains:
goodonyou.go2cloud.org
tracking.goodonyou.eco
www.km0trk.com
You can opt-out of this tracking on brand and retailer websites by blocking cookies on those websites in your browser.
More Information
If you are still looking for more information, you can contact us through one of our preferred contact methods.
