info@goodonyou.eco
or via the postal address at the end of this policy.
3. Using your personal information
Personal information submitted to Good On You by any means including via the Good On You app, via any digital product or tool, via the Good On You website, or given to us via email or phone, will be used for the purposes specified in this privacy and cookies policy or in relevant parts of the website, app or other digital product or tool.
We may use your personal information to:
administer the website, app and digital product or tools;
improve your experience by personalising the website, app or digital product or tool;
enable your use of the services available;
seek your views or comments on the services we provide;
notify you of changes to our services;
market research, internal monitoring and traffic auditing. This information is only examined in aggregate;
send to you goods purchased (if and when that function becomes available) and supply to you services purchased;
deliver customisable content to you as a user;
send statements and invoices to you, and collect payments from you;
send you general (non-marketing) and non-commercial communications;
send you email, in app or mobile phone notifications which you have specifically requested;
send you our newsletter and other marketing communications relating to Good On You;
help you understand and improve your Good On You rating;
provide third parties with anonymous statistical information about our website users – this information will not be used to identify any individual user;
if and when it is introduced, process financial transactions through our payment services provider, Stripe. We will share information with Stripe only to the extent necessary for the purposes of processing payments you make via our website and dealing with complaints and queries relating to such payments; and
process a job application; and
(where information has been provided for a particular purpose) to give effect to or facilitate that purpose.
